There are indications that President Muhammadu Buhari has decided to intervene in the crises that is rocking the unity of the All Progressive Congress (APC), as he has summoned a meeting of some APC governors. The meeting coming barely  24 hours after the formation of the Reformed All Progressive Congress by aggrieved APC members is said to be critical  to finding solution to the problem BusinessDay gathered that the netting is being attended by Abubakar Badaru of Jigawa state, Abdulaziz Yari of Zamfara state and Abubakar Bagudu of Kebbi state. Recall that every efforts by the aggrieved rAPC members to meet with the President previously had proved abortive It is however not clear what the meeting Being held behind closed doors will come up with  Details later…